$ Power Query Editor: File -> Options & Settings -> Query Options

{ Global

  { Data Load

    Type Detection: Choose one of
      • Always detect column types and headers for unstructured sources
      • Detect column types and headers for unstructured soruces according to each file's setting
      • Never detect column types and headers for unstructued sources

    Default Query Load Settings
      • Use standard load settings
      • Specify custom default load settings (Load to worksheet or Load to Data Model)
      • Fast data Load

    Data Cache management Options

    Clear cache

  }
  { Power Query Editor

     Layout: Tick or untick
       • Display the Query Settings pane
       • Display the Formula Bar

     Data Preview
       • Display preview contents using a monospaced font
       • Show whitespace and newline characters

     Parameters
       • Always allow parameterization in data source and transformation dialogs

     Formula
       • Enable M Intellisense in the formula bar, advanced editor, and custom column dialog.

  }
  { Security

    Native Database Queries
      • Require use approval for new native database queries

    Certificate Revocation Check
      • Enable certificate revocation check

    Web Preview Warning Level
      • Strict
      • Moderate
      • None

    Approved ADFS Authentication Services

  }
  { Privacy

    Privacy Levels
      • Always combine data according to your Privacy Level settings for each source
      • Combine data according to each file's Privacy Level settings
      • Always ignore Privacy level setting

  }
  { Diagnostic Options

    Diagnostic Options:
      • Enable tracing

    Enable or disable Crash Dump Collection

    *See also* the → Microsoft/Power-Query/M-formula/standard-library/Diagnostics/Trace[standard library function `Diagnostics.Trace`].

  }


}
{ Current Workbook

  { Data Load

    Type Detection
      • Detect column types and headers for unstructured sources
    
    Relationships
      • Create relationships between tables when adding to the Data Model for the first time
      • Update relationships when refreshing queries loaded to the Data Model

    Background Data
      • Allow data preview to download in the background

  }
  { Regional Settings

    Locale

  }
  { Privacy

    Privacy Levels
      • Combine data according to your Privacy Level settings for each source
      • Ignore the Privacy levels and potentially improve performance


  }

